                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Some studies attempted to detect disease in tomato plants. Moghadam et al. [298] proposed a probabilistic model, which combined the vegetation indices of two ranges (VNIR and SWIR) to detect the Spotted Wilt Virus in the plants. The data were collected using two headwall brand push room cameras, namely the VNIR- A series and SWIR- M series [298]. The spectral range was "
