                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Although the aforementioned studies achieved satisfactory performance for disease detection, some challenges still need to be considered. First, machine- learning- or deep- learning- based algorithms require large data. Insufficient data and class imbalances can significantly lower the performance of the models [300]. Therefore, it is essential to ensure the quality of the data before machine learning algorithms are used for disease detection."
