                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "2) Disease Classification: The main goal of disease classification is to classify the pathogens or disease types obtained from hyperspectral images. Classification of diseased and healthy plants by employing the nondestructive technique is relatively challenging to comprehend the early symptoms of diseases. This is because several disease symptoms may visually look similar to each other. Simultaneously, single pathogen-infected"
                                }
